translation.p:
(V. 8.) Wise men (and gods) praise him as Hari (himself); because indeed he offers
protection to (all) living beings (as Hari preserves within his own self the rudiments of life);
loves truth (as Hari loves his consort Satyā); is victorious (Jishṇu); firm (Achyuta);
glorious (as Hari is united with Śrī i.e. Lakshmī) and is, among men (possessed) of a
lovely body (as Hari is an embodiment of Death to the demon Naraka).
